definitions.definition: ( intransitive ) To have enough courage (to do something).
examples: I wouldn't dare (to) argue with my boss.
No one dares (to) criticize his decisions.

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To defy or challenge (someone to do something).
examples: I dare you to kiss that girl.

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To have enough courage to meet or do something, go somewhere, etc.; to face up to .
examples: Will you dare death to reach your goal?

definitions.definition: ( archaic , transitive ) To drive larks to the ground by scaring them (for instance, with mirrors or hawks) so they can be caught in nets.

definitions.definition: To stare stupidly or vacantly; to gaze as though amazed or terrified .
To lie or crouch down in fear .
